WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.000
Hello everyone, welcome to the meeting.

00:00:04.000 --> 00:00:08.500
Today we will discuss the project timeline.

00:00:08.500 --> 00:00:12.000
John will present the initial proposal.

00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:16.000
After that, we will open the floor for questions.

00:00:16.000 --> 00:00:20.000
Thank you all for joining.

00:00:20.000 --> 00:00:45.000
Thanks for the intro. As you know, the current target is to launch the new API by April 15th. Based on the latest sprint, we are about 70% complete.

00:00:45.000 --> 00:01:10.000
The remaining work is mainly in the authentication module — specifically the token refresh logic and rate limiting.

00:01:10.000 --> 00:01:35.000
From the testing side, we still have 12 open bugs that we need to resolve before we can go live.

00:01:35.000 --> 00:02:00.000
Sarah: John, if we stick to April 15th, we would have to ship with known issues. That feels risky.

00:02:00.000 --> 00:02:25.000
Michael: Agreed. Marketing has also raised concerns. A broken launch could damage our brand reputation.

00:02:25.000 --> 00:02:50.000
John: So what are our realistic options here?

00:02:50.000 --> 00:03:15.000
We can either delay the launch by two weeks or release with limited features and roll out the rest later.

00:03:15.000 --> 00:03:40.000
Sarah: Delaying is better than launching something unstable. A bad first impression will hurt us more in the long run.

00:03:40.000 --> 00:04:05.000
Michael: That makes sense. Are we all aligned on delaying the full launch?

00:04:05.000 --> 00:04:20.000
Yes, I agree.

00:04:20.000 --> 00:04:35.000
Agreed.

00:04:35.000 --> 00:04:50.000
Yes, let's delay.

00:04:50.000 --> 00:05:15.000
John: Okay, decision made — we will delay the full API launch to May 1st.

00:05:15.000 --> 00:05:40.000
Next, we need to make sure all critical bugs are fixed before the new deadline.

00:05:40.000 --> 00:06:05.000
Sarah: Vikram, can you take ownership of the token refresh issue?

00:06:05.000 --> 00:06:30.000
Vikram: Yes, I’ll fix it and push an update by April 10th.

00:06:30.000 --> 00:06:55.000
John: Great. Ananya, can you oversee the final end-to-end testing?

00:06:55.000 --> 00:07:20.000
Ananya: Sure, I will complete all testing by April 20th.

00:07:20.000 --> 00:07:45.000
Michael: We also need updated feature documentation from the tech team.

00:07:45.000 --> 00:08:10.000
Vikram: We’ll provide the final documentation by April 12th.

00:08:10.000 --> 00:08:35.000
John: Noted. Let’s also keep a 3-day buffer before the May 1st launch in case any last-minute bugs appear.

00:08:35.000 --> 00:09:00.000
Everyone: Sounds good.

00:09:00.000 --> 00:09:30.000
John: Alright, let me summarize: API launch delayed to May 1st, Vikram fixes token refresh by April 10th, Ananya completes testing by April 20th, and documentation delivered by April 12th.

00:09:30.000 --> 00:09:50.000
Any other concerns before we close?

00:09:50.000 --> 00:10:05.000
No, we're good.

00:10:05.000 --> 00:10:25.000
Thank you everyone. Meeting adjourned.